es of lifting accessories:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li>Slings<\/li><li>Hooks<\/li><li>Shackles<\/li><li>Spreader beams<\/li><li>Eyebolts<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">The Importance of having a lifting equipment inspection<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Lifting equipment perform lots of gruelling tasks, and because they are well-constructed, some perform hundreds of operations per day. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>But no matter how well they are designed, these routine jobs will naturally begin to cause the equipment to degrade over time.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are some of the reasons why you should always have your lifting machines regularly inspected:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li><strong>To avoid machine failure<\/strong><\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>This is probably the most important reason of all; stopping machinery failure that could lead to life-threatening accidents for workers and everyone on-site.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Regular inspection will help detect traces of damage including when equipment is rusted or broken. Remember, just because your machines appear to be fine doesn\u2019t mean they are functioning optimally.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Regular inspection of lifting equipment will help ensure that every single component of your machine is sound and fully operational.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li><strong>Boosts productivity<\/strong><\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Truth is, even when a single element in your machine breakdowns, it becomes difficult to operate productively or fully complete tasks.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You have clients to serve, you have deadlines to beat, so it\u2019s a no-brainer that when there\u2019s an equipment failure, the workflow is disrupted and, in some occasions, projects are completely halted\u2026 those are productive hours gone down the drain.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>If only you had scheduled an inspection earlier, such issues would have been averted and productivity would have possibly doubled.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li><strong>Ensures compliance with industry standards and regulations<\/strong><\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Let\u2019s take a moment to remind ourselves that first, it is every employer\u2019s responsibility to create a safe working environment for their employees.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Because every employee\u2019s life is greatly important, there are different regulations that govern lifting equipment with the aim of making sure that safety hazards are eliminated or else the employer incurs hefty fines.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Taking advantage of the services of a professional to inspect your lifting equipment regularly will help cut down technical damages, ensure you don\u2019t spend your hard-earned money on unnecessary hefty fines, and help you stay compliant with industrial standards.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Conclusion<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Having your equipment functioning at peak performance is very vital and lifting equipment inspection has a huge role to play in this.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Break the habit of using your lifting equipment for years without checking whether they\u2019re in good shape or not.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>At Emobella Engineering Nig. Ltd., we provide <a href=\"https:\/\/lejiccal.com\/lifting-equipment\/\">lifting equipment inspection services<\/a> to help protect your assets and prolong their lifespan, while ensuring the safety of your employees. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Our inspectors are among the foremost experienced in the industry and are qualified to perform all structural, periodic, or annual inspections. <a href=\"https:\/\/lejiccal.com\/contact\/\">Contact us today<\/a> to discuss your next lifting equipment inspection project.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Lifting Equipment Lifting equipment are equipment and accessories that are carefully designed to assist lifting, loading, or unloading of heavy goods and personnel at work. As they work directly with goods, properties and human lives, the importance of having a functional and sa